data.prose: A psychologist shows two different short videos to test subjects, and asked them to rate their feelings after the video as Happiness, Anger or Sadness:
data.question: whether emotional reactions are independent of the choice of video.
data.null: Emotional reactions are independent of the choice of video.
data.alternative: Emotional reactions are not independent of the choice of video.
data.claim: We reject the null hypothesis and accept the alternative hypothesis,

data.prose: Two tech companies, Company A and B, recruit students from Universities 1, 2 and 3.  A sampling on recent hires show their Alma Mater:
data.question: whether hiring preferences of the companies are independent of the company.
data.null: Hiring preferences are independent of the company.
data.alternative: Hiring preferences are not independent of the company.
